Sentencas: BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta (BZY) layers with various thicknesses ( similar to 0.7, similar to 1.7, similar to 2.4 and similar to 3.6 mu m) are fabricated using the pulsed laser deposition (PLD) technique on anode-supported BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta (BCY) electrolyte films.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-δ-BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ bilayer electrolyte for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta-SDC (SSC-SDC, 70:30 wt.%) cathode is applied onto the BZY/BCY bilayer electrolyte to form a single cell.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-δ-BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ bilayer electrolyte for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The chemical stability of the BZY/BCY bilayer electrolytes improves with increasing BZY layer thickness.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-δ-BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ bilayer electrolyte for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The BZY ( similar to 3.6 mu m)/BCY bilayer electrolyte shows an excellent chemical stability after treated in 100% CO2 atmosphere at 900 C.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-δ-BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ bilayer electrolyte for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of 447, 370, 276, 218 and 163 mW cm(-2) are measured with the BZY layer thicknesses of 0, 0.7, 1.7, 2.4 and 3.6 mu m at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-δ-BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ bilayer electrolyte for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In general, the BZY/BCY bilayer electrolyte cell with an optimum BZY layer thickness can improve chemical stability without great influence on the electrochemical performance for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-δ-BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ bilayer electrolyte for anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
